verbose_text: This can also be exhibited in Fig. XREF_FIG where it can be seen that the amount of WEA associated with the cracks increases across 4-18 h, an increase being observed between 12 and 18 h. Further to this, by visually observing the mapped WECs at 4 and 6 h a decrease in WEA volume is seen at the start and ends of the WEC, i.e. the extreme tips when visualised as a 3D network.
